					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">In software, ((period &lt;&lt; 1) | 0x001) is identical in effect to ((period &lt;&lt; 1) + 0x001). It just takes fewer gates in hardware to OR rather than add.
<br />
<br />The key hypothesis that I'm making is that it doesn't count down and reset the counter on the same cycle. So (x * 2 + 1) cycles of counting down followed by 1 cycle of resetting (and not counting down) equals the observed (x * 2 + 2) cycles.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

